<section id="fs-idp41022080" class="critical-thinking">
  <title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
  <exercise id="fs-idp71692576">
    <problem id="fs-idp73377072">
      <para id="fs-idp43217536">Do you think it is rational for workers to prefer sticky wages to wage cuts, when the consequence of sticky wages is unemployment for some workers? Why or why not? How do the reasons for sticky wages explained in this section apply to your argument?</para>
    </problem>
  </exercise>
</section>


<section id="fs-idp71167488" class="problems">
